cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SE 

This paper is about an architecture for managing digital objects and their relationships, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper specifically mentions digital libraries as one of the end-user applications for the architecture. The second most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the architecture includes a triple store for querying relationships among objects. The third likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the architecture is designed for managing and disseminating complex objects. The fourth likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper discusses the open-source nature of the software and its potential impact on various institutions. The fifth likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper describes the implementation of the architecture as a web service with REST and SOAP interfaces.
